Fast HTTP Vulnerability Scanner Data Structures

Here are the data structures with brief descriptions:
_cb_list
_dataThis struct stores information to an HTTP request or response. Both HTTP Headers and HTTP body data are stored under this struct
_hhandleThis struct is the information used by FHScan to manage HTTP requests. This struct does not manage sockets, however a pointer to an STABLISHED_CONNECTION is provided. For the user point of view, this handle is only a pointer. an user must not tweak data stored in this struct
_HTTPmapping_struct_
_requestThis struct handles information related to and http response and includes information about client request, server response, url, server version .returned by an HTTP Server
